        "---\n",
        "## 🔌 Section 2 — Technical Implementation: Model Context Protocol (MCP)\n",
        "\n",
        "### What is MCP?\n",
        "\n",
        "The **Model Context Protocol** is an open standard (introduced by Anthropic, 2024) that\n",
        "defines a uniform way for AI agents to discover and call external tools — analogous to\n",
        "how HTTP standardises web communication.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Why MCP?\n",
        "| Without MCP | With MCP |\n",
        "|-------------|----------|\n",
        "| Each agent hard-codes tool calls | Agents query a registry and call tools by name |\n",
        "| Adding a tool requires code changes in every agent | Register once; all agents can discover it |\n",
        "| No standard error envelope | Consistent `is_error` + `content` response |\n",
        "| Difficult to audit tool invocations | Every call logged with ID, timestamp, inputs, outputs |\n",
        "\n",
        "### MCP Protocol Flow (as implemented here)\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "Agent                      MCPToolRegistry (in-process MCP Server)\n",
        "  │                                │\n",
        "  │──── initialize() ──────────────▶  Register capabilities\n",
        "  │◀─── {tools: [...schemas]} ─────│\n",
        "  │                                │\n",
        "  │──── tools/list ────────────────▶\n",
        "  │◀─── [{name, description,       │\n",
        "  │       inputSchema}]            │\n",
        "  │                                │\n",
        "  │──── tools/call ────────────────▶  Execute tool function\n",
        "  │     {name, arguments}          │  Validate inputs against JSON schema\n",
        "  │◀─── {content, isError} ────────│  Return MCP-envelope result\n",
        "  │                                │\n",
        "  │──── get_audit_log() ───────────▶\n",
        "  │◀─── [{call_id, tool, ts, …}]   │  Full audit trail\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "### MCP Tool Schema (JSON Schema subset)\n",
        "Each tool exposes:\n",
        "- **`name`** — unique identifier\n",
        "- **`description`** — natural-language description for the routing agent\n",
        "- **`inputSchema`** — JSON Schema object describing required/optional parameters\n"
      ],
